  "chunk_index": 19,
  "summary": "Following the inquest, Major Melrose drives Bondel back to Chimney House while Jimmy returns to London. Disturbed by Bondel's account of the events, Jimmy calls Lorna to inform her that the inquest ruled the death an accident, though he suspects a cover-up. He warns Lorna to be careful, prompting her to express concern for his own safety. Jimmy then instructs his associate, Stevens, to procure an automatic handgun with a blued barrel.\n\nOn Friday afternoon, Bondel attends a gala at the Two-Footed Dragon Church. George Lomax greets her warmly, and Jimmy arrives, appearing more serious than usual. Jimmy whispers to Bondel that he has informed Bill about their \"little scheme,\" though Bondel expresses frustration with Bill's perceived lack of intelligence.\n\nDuring the event, George introduces Bondel to several guests, including Sir Stanley Digby, Mr. O'Roke, Mr. Osborne, Lady Cutt, Mr. Bettman, and the Countess Razky. While Lady Cutt discusses a recent car accident with Jimmy, Sir Oswald Kuter discusses property with Bondel, expressing interest in Chimney House, which leaves her feeling indignant. \n\nAfter changing her clothes, Bondel encounters a bulky man dressed as a butler. She identifies him as Detective Inspector Bartholomew, who has arrived in disguise to protect Mr. Lomax following a threatening letter. Bondel finds his disguise unconvincing, but the Inspector remains undeterred.",
